<TEXT>
<P>
 I always read the Food Section of the L.A. Times. Don't know why -- I'm a 
lousy cook. I guess I like to read about what other people go through.I also 
read the restaurant reviews -- just in case I can ever get my husband to eat 
out. 
</P>
<P>
 But I'm especially glad I read Doris Silverton's story, "Lord God King of the 
Universe and President of the Motion Picture Academy" (March 24). It was 
wonderful. I really laughed out loud. Not only is she a wonderful writer, but 
my husband was born in Italy and had old-country parents. In family 
relationships, the Jewish and Italian cultures are so much alike. The story 
brought back many happy and funny memories. 
</P>
<P>
 JEAN ROSSO 
</P>
