<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Japanese Official Sees End of Recession: In the most authoritative official 
statement yet that Japan's economic outlook is improving, Bank of Japan 
Governor Yasushi Mieno said Japan's worst postwar recession appears to be 
drawing to a close."The economy is brighter," Mieno said after conclusion of a 
three-day conference of the bank's branch managers. Participants in the meeting 
confirmed evidence of improved corporate sentiment and recovery in personal 
consumption, he said. Mieno warned, however, that the economy is still in the 
process of bottoming out and that a quick recovery is not assured. He cited the 
strong yen and trade frictions as factors that could cut off any recovery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
