<P>
WHALES: THE NEED FOR THE HUMAN TOUCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As to the person putting the captions on the pictures for your article on 
whales (April 24), "Exhibiting the Human Touch," they should have read the 
article first. 
</P>
<P>
 The picture on pages 12 and 13 is captioned, "A whale nuzzles up to a boat and 
the outstretched hands of humans.During mating season off Baja, whales enjoy 
the contact." During mating season you risk getting capsized (or getting hit by 
a 10-foot-long penis) if you are near the whales. It should have read, "During 
nursing season. . . ." All the adult gray whale males have long since departed 
the lagoons for their migration north while the mothers nurse their young. 
</P>
<P>
 Other than the above, I congratulate your staff for an excellent article. 
</P>
<P>
 I kissed a whale. 
</P>
<P>
 VIVIAN RICHMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Malibu  
