<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; CHILDREN'S BUREAU SEEKS FOSTER PARENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Children's Bureau of Southern California is seeking foster parents who 
will provide short- or long-term care for babies, toddlers and school-age 
children. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested are invited to attend a special orientation session Tuesday 
at Lampson Elementary School in Garden Grove.The session will begin at 6:30 
p.m. at the school, 13321 Lampson Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The Children's Bureau is especially looking for Spanish-speaking foster 
parents who are willing to work with children and their biological parents.  
</P>
<P>
 Those selected as foster parents will receive training, certification and 
funding to aid in caring for the children, officials at the Children's Bureau 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 They said thousands of Orange County children are reported as abused or 
neglected each year and most could benefit from being placed in the care of 
loving foster families. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone interested in becoming a foster parent is asked to call (714) 
385-9025.MIMI KO 
</P>
