<HEADLINE>
<P>
MUSICK GETS 300TH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley Coach Herschel Musick celebrated his 300th victory after a 
nail biter that ended with the Falcons scoring all their runs in the seventh 
inning for a 5-4 Century League victory over Villa Park Wednesday at Santa Ana 
Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Musick, who started the school's program in 1959, is 300-262-2. 
</P>
<P>
 With one out, Robert Serrano, who pitched a complete game, drove in Freddy 
Macias with the winning run after hitting a long drive that bounced off the 
right-field fence. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley improved to 7-7, 2-2. Villa Park dropped to 7-7, 1-3. 
</P>
