<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; ORANGE COAST WINS IN 12TH TO STOP FULLERTON'S STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It took 12 innings but Orange Coast became the first team to beat Fullerton in 
an Orange Empire Conference softball game this season, Wednesday at Orange 
Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Kallemeyn scored on a fielder's choice on a ball hit by April Crosby with 
one out in the 12th to give the Pirates a 2-1 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory moves Orange Coast (21-10-2, 8-2 in conference) within a game of 
Fullerton (19-11, 9-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton was coming off a 1-0 victory over Riverside Tuesday night. Alicia 
Robles had pitched a no-hitter for the Hornets in that game and held OCC 
hitless for the first 5 1/3 innings Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton started the conference with a 4-1 victory over Cypress then won the 
next eight conference games by shutouts. 
</P>
<P>
 But Orange Coast broke the streak when Kelsi Armbruster singled home Nicole 
Shammas in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton rallied to tie it in the seventh. Melissa Graham and Tricia Wedekind 
singled and moved up on a sacrifice by Kathy Donovan. Dee Dee Miranda bunted 
for a hit to load the bases and the tying run scored on a fielder's choice. 
</P>
<P>
 Kallemeyn stated OCC's winning rally with a single up the middle. Stefanie 
Ritchey then bunted for a hit and the runners moved up on an error. 
</P>
<P>
 Crosby slapped the ball off the end of the bat to Fullerton first baseman 
Miranda who threw late to home. 
</P>
<P>
 Kristen Varagne (5-3) got the victory in relief and Robles (14-7) took the 
loss. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
