<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISSOURI VOTERS REJECT SLOT MACHINE WAGERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Missouri voters Tuesday narrowly defeated a constitutional amendment that 
would have allowed slot machines on riverboats. 
</P>
<P>
 The amendment would have lifted the ban in the Missouri Constitution on "games 
of chance." 
</P>
<P>
 Riverboat owners can still get a state license to offer so-called games of 
skill, such as poker or blackjack. 
</P>
