<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE CHIEFS BACK WILSON'S REELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citing a shared philosophy of more police and tougher anti-crime laws, the Los 
Angeles Police Chiefs Assn. on Wednesday endorsed Gov. Pete Wilson's reelection 
bid. 
</P>
<P>
 "When Pete Wilson says that every Californian has a fundamental right not to 
become a crime victim and not to live in fear -- these are the words of a 
fighter, not a liberal politician with no record on crime," said Hawthorne 
Police Chief Stephen Port, president of the group that represents more than 40 
police chiefs in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
 The endorsement followed a meeting between Wilson and several police chiefs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
