<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COLLEGE DISTRICT LISTS '94 PRIORITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Maintaining campus buildings and improving students' access to financial aid 
topped the list of priorities approved this week by trustees of the Ventura 
County Community College District. 
</P>
<P>
 The trustees compiled the list in an attempt to define the scope and 
importance of the issues they hope to tackle in 1994.The final version, with 
the objectives listed by priority, was released at the district board meeting 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Improving the safety and durability of campus buildings made the list, 
trustees said, because college officials have repeatedly insisted that many 
campus facilities are in need of repair. 
</P>
<P>
 Increasing financial aid access also topped the district's priorities, they 
said, because there is evidence that students are not enrolling at the district 
because they cannot get their financial aid soon enough or they are not aware 
they are eligible for financial aid. 
</P>
<P>
 Also high on the list were research to assess student achievement at the 
district, computerization of student registration and improvement of campus 
parking facilities. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
