<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; CAUSE OF BOY'S DEATH REMAINS UNKNOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County coroner's office has autopsied the body of a 
15-year-old Thousand Oaks boy who collapsed and died on a school soccer field 
Monday, but results of the exam were inconclusive, an official said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Coroner's officials are waiting to review old medical records and new test 
results on tissue samples from the autopsy of Giwook Lee before declaring the 
cause of his death, said Scott Carrier, a spokesman for the coroner's office. 
</P>
