 Lee, an eighth-grader at Colina Intermediate School in Thousand Oaks whom 
friends described as friendly and outgoing, had been playing soccer during the 
lunch hour Monday when he collapsed. 
</P>
<P>
 School employees performed cardiopulmonary resuscitation on Lee until 
paramedics arrived and took him to Westlake Medical Center, where he was 
pronounced dead Monday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Hospital officials said information from Lee's family indicated that he 
suffered from a congenital heart problem. MACK REED 
