<HEADLINE>
<P>
CFL TEAM WILL LOOK AT MARINOVICH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former USC and Raider quarterback Todd Marinovich is expected to try out with 
the Winnipeg Blue Bombers of the Canadian Football League on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Marinovich, who was unavailable for comment, has dropped out of sight since 
being released by the Raiders before to the start of last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Marinovich has not yet signed a contract with Winnipeg. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blue Bombers are also expected to look at Charlie Ward, formerly of 
Florida State, Kevin McDougal, formerly of Notre Dame, during the three-day 
tryout camp at Martin, Tenn. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
