<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS; MONROVIA; 3 BUILDING PROJECTS; SCHEDULED FOR THIS YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials have reached agreement with a developer to turn the site of a 
former Buick dealership at Huntington Drive and the Foothill Freeway into 
restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 Groundbreaking is expected this month for the Claim Jumper Restaurant, 
scheduled to open later this year. It will join a chain of 12 Southland 
restaurants.  
</P>
<P>
 Monrovia will also be home to a new medical plaza at the corner of Huntington 
Drive and Ivy Avenue and a two-rink ice stadium complex on Fifth Avenue this 
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
