<P>
CITY HALL NEWS; ARCADIA; OFFICIAL'S CARWASH CLEANS CITY'S FLEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A carwash business owned by an Arcadia councilman seeking reelection Tuesday 
has received more than $40,000 from the city in his last four years of office 
for cleaning the city's fleet of cars, city records show. Fasching's Car Wash, 
owned by George Fasching, reportedly netted $41,743 while he was on the 
council. 
</P>
<P>
 The councilman voted four times to approve a vehicle maintenance budget that 
included cleaning of city cars and vans at his own facility. The city attorney 
said although conflict of interest is not a crime, he will advise that if 
Fasching is reelected, the councilman should abstain from voting on the issue 
in the city budget. 
</P>
<P>
 Fasching's defenders said that his carwash is the only one in town and that 
the business cleaned the city's cars for several years before Fasching was 
elected. But the councilman's critics pointed to a new carwash on the 
Arcadia/Temple City border, which is not getting the city's business. 
</P>
<P>
 Fasching said his carwash has cleaned the city's cars for 12 to 14 years and 
that he gives the city a discount of $2.25 per vehicle because it buys blocks 
of tickets. "I do a favor for the city," he said. 
</P>
