<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WHITTIER; BURGLAR SENTENCED TO LIFE FOR KILLING WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man has been sentenced to life in prison without the possibility of parole 
for stabbing a Whittier woman to death in front of her 5-year-old 
granddaughter. 
</P>
<P>
 David Anthony Martinez, 25, of Whittier had pleaded not guilty by reason of 
insanity.But jurors found that he was sane when he broke into the house of 
52-year-old Romelia Salas on Comstock Avenue and stabbed her more than 20 times 
Oct. 26, 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 After a one-week trial in Norwalk Superior Court, the jury found Martinez 
guilty of first-degree murder and burglary. Superior Court Judge Philip H. 
Hickok sentenced Martinez last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The child witnessed the attack, then locked herself in a bedroom as Martinez 
remained in the house through the night, according to a statement from the 
district attorney's office. The child ran to tell neighbors in the morning. 
</P>
