<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS / CRIME; MAN HELD ON CHILD PORN CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE DONNELLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Ontario man who worked as a campus supervisor at a San Dimas center for 
abused children was arrested Tuesday on charges of misdemeanor possession of 
child pornography, including a large supply of magazines and videos, Ontario 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Edward Kochevar, 25, is being held at San Bernardino County's West 
Valley Detention Center on $100,000 bail.Ontario police originally arrested 
Kochevar March 21 after police searched his home and allegedly found the 
pornographic material.  
</P>
<P>
 Kochevar was released, then rearrested Tuesday after police finally sorted 
through and presented the mass of alleged evidence. 
</P>
<P>
 Kochevar worked at the McKinley Home for Boys -- a residential treatment 
center for abused children -- for four months before his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 Executive Director Jane Van Stedum said Kochevar has been suspended 
indefinitely. Van Stedum also said none of the children complained of problems 
with Kochevar during interviews the center conducted after his arrest. Kochevar 
is a trained child care worker who came to McKinley "with great references" and 
passed a standard background check for sex offenses, Van Stedum said. JOE 
DONNELLY 
</P>
