<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONTEREY PARK: COST OF CONTRACTOR SELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A few weeks ago, I read a letter to the editor regarding the use of the 
renovated El Encanto facility in the city of Monterey Park.The criticism of the 
possible uses was one thing, but I know some of the facts were missing. When 
the selection of the contractor first came before the City Council, it was 
Councilman Fred Balderrama who exposed the contractor's poor performance record 
and protested their "D"-rated bond. 
</P>
<P>
 A few months later, the contractor failed to do his job and now it is costing 
the taxpayers an additional $200,000. This thanks to Councilman Sam Kiang, who 
made the motion to grant the contract to the less-qualified contractor. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN WANG 
</P>
<P>
 Monterey Park  
</P>
