 The Cal Poly Pomona's baseball team, ranked 24th in NCAA Division II, entered 
the week 21-13-1, 6-3 in the California Collegiate Athletic Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The Broncos travel to Cal State Dominguez Hills Friday and play host to the 
Toros twice Saturday in a three-game CCAA series. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, Pomona lost two of three CCAA games against Cal Poly San Luis 
Obispo. Pomona, San Luis Obispo and Dominguez Hills are tied for first place in 
the CCAA. 
</P>
<P>
 Pomona senior designated hitter Dave Anderlik is batting .424. Junior 
outfielder Aaron Edwards is batting .388 with 29 stolen bases. 
</P>
