 FDA Unit Finds Calgene Tomato Is Safe to Eat: At a three-day hearing in 
Washington to review the Food and Drug Administration's policies on 
bioengineered foods, the agency's Center for Food Safety and Applied Nutrition 
called the Davis, Calif., biotechnology company's tomato "as safe as other 
currently consumed tomatoes." Calgene is still awaiting formal FDA approval to 
market the gene-altered tomato. The agency may introduce regulations requiring 
that it be notified by food companies intending to sell such products. 
