<P>
 Quake Losses Prompt Ratings Review for Farmers Group: Insurance rating agency 
A. M. Best Co. said it placed Farmers Insurance Group's "A" (Excellent) rating 
under review because of Farmers' announced $600 million in gross claims from 
the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake.Best estimated that quake claims would wipe 
out 15% of Farmers' capital. Best said it expected to complete its review next 
month after evaluating the insurer's efforts to bolster its surplus and reduce 
its exposure to catastrophe losses. Los Angeles-based Farmers is California's 
third-largest carrier of property and casualty insurance. 
