<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Research Branch Opens: Roper Starch Worldwide, one of the oldest names in 
market research, has opened a West Coast office in Newport Beach. The company, 
which conducted the most recent study for Kinsey on American sexuality, has 
worked for such clients here as Foote, Cone & Belding; Honda, Apple Computers 
and Sega.Running the West Coast operation is Albert J. Yesk, formerly director 
of the Newport Beach office of market researcher Albemarle Yankelovich Clancy 
Shulman. Yesk spent 29 years with his former firm. "There's a lot of business 
here, the economy's coming back, and we feel it's a good time" for a West Coast 
office, Yesk said. "This is a company that was trying to do it all from the 
East." Roper Starch, which is based in Mamaroneck, N.Y., has affiliates in 33 
other countries. 
</P>
