<TEXT>
<P>
 Course Maker Bought: National Education Corp. said Monday that it has paid 
about $4 million for MicroMash, a Denver-based maker of computer courses on 
accounting.Jerome W. Cwiertnia, National Education's president and chief 
executive officer, said the MicroMash acquisition positions his company in the 
continuing professional education arena. With 50 employees, MicroMash offers 
more than 60 courses of study in accounting, including candidate preparation 
for various examinations, such as the Certified Public Accountant examination. 
National Education Corp. in Irvine provides multimedia educational training 
products in engineering, business, technology and other areas. The company, 
with 3,800 employees, lost $9.6 million in fiscal 1993 on sales of $355 
million. 
</P>
