<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MONTEREY PARK/ ROSEMEAD; SOROPTIMISTS OFFER SCHOLARSHIP FOR 
CITIZEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Soroptimist International of Monterey Park/Rosemead is accepting applications 
for its annual scholarship for a financially needy student in the area who is a 
U.S. citizen.Applicants may be male or female and must have completed one year 
of college. 
</P>
<P>
 Financial need does not necessarily require a low income because of high 
tuition at some schools. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at the Monterey Park Chamber of Commerce, 163 W. 
Garvey Ave., or Bruggemeyer Memorial Library, 318 S. Ramona Ave., Monterey 
Park, and the Rosemead Chamber of Commerce, 3953 Muscatel Ave., or by calling 
(818) 308-2380. Applications must be postmarked no later than April 29. 
</P>
