<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; ARMORY CENTER LENDS SPACE FOR ART SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Armory Center for the Arts in Pasadena will lend some of its space to Cal 
State Northridge for an exhibit of pen-and-ink drawings and prints by Sudanese 
artist Mohamed Omer Bushara. 
</P>
<P>
 The show was scheduled to open at the university shortly after the Jan. 17 
earthquake, which severely damaged the campus and its art gallery. Officials at 
the university contacted the armory about borrowing space. 
</P>
<P>
 The exhibition will run Tuesday through Sunday, noon to 5 p.m., through April 
24. Admission is free. Information: (818) 792-5101. 
</P>
