<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SAN DIMAS; AVERAGE MONTHLY WATER BILL TO RISE ABOUT $7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Public Utilities Commission has approved a revenue increase for 
the Southern California Water Co.'s San Dimas district. 
</P>
<P>
 Water rates for the 15,000 customers in San Dimas and Charter Oak will 
increase by 23 cents per 100 cubic feet, with an additional temporary surcharge 
of 7 cents per 100 cubic feet for two years. 
</P>
<P>
 The average monthly bill for 2,300 cubic feet of water will rise from $32.91 
to $39.87. The new rates took effect in March.) 
</P>
</TEXT>
