<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 63 SERVICE GROUPS TO GET DISNEY AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Disneyland will hand out $300,000 to 63 Orange County service organizations at 
its annual Community Service Awards luncheon today. 
</P>
<P>
 In its 37th year, the Disney awards salute the work of deserving nonprofit 
organizations in Orange County.Service organizations in 10 categories will be 
recognized: Cultural Arts, Educational, Service for Youth, Accomplishments by 
Youth Groups, Special Health Services, Accomplishments by Support Groups, 
Social Community Service, Civic Community Service, Service By or For Senior 
Citizens, and Environment, Ecology and Energy. 
</P>
<P>
 In each category, there will be five awards of $3,000, and one of $7,000. In 
addition, two groups will receive the $15,000 Special Judges Award, and one 
organization will receive the Outstanding Award of $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Lunch, which is free to attending service organization members, will be served 
at noon, and the awards presentation starts at 1 p.m. The event is being held 
in the Grand Ballroom at the Disneyland Hotel, 1150 W. Cerritos Ave., Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (714) 999-4834. 
</P>
</TEXT>
