<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: REDONDO BEACH; REJECTION OF PET LAW PUTS MAN IN HOG HEAVEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kyle Kazan was fuming. 
</P>
<P>
 The owner of a pot-bellied pig had read in a local paper that Redondo Beach 
was considering a ban on the animals this week.So he hoofed down to the council 
chambers Tuesday night determined to raise a stink. 
</P>
<P>
 "They're not smelly animals, they're not loud," Kazan told the council. "Your 
dogs will bark much louder than pigs can oink." 
</P>
<P>
 Mindful of his concerns and those of other pet owners, the council Tuesday 
rejected a proposed law that not only would have banned more pigs, but also 
would have prohibited anyone from owning four or more pets (an aquarium would 
have counted as a single pet). 
</P>
<P>
 Kazan, who walks his pig Oink through town at least once a week, was in hog 
heaven. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm not very political, but I felt I had to come down because they were 
picking on pigs," said Kazan, 27. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said they will handle future pet problems on a case-by-case 
basis. JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
