<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIDBITS; SPUDS: YOGURT SHOP ADDS NEW MACHINES, ONE TO GRIND UP SOME CREATIVE 
CONCOCTIONS MADE OF BAKED POTATOES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEO SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura's Cafe Yogurt & More just added some more more. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, owner Cheri Burk unveiled two identical machines, one to produce an 
array of baked potatoes, the other to spit out a multitude of soft-serve yogurt 
and ice-cream flavors. 
</P>
<P>
 The spud machine will allow her to create made-to-order potatoes by mixing 
potato meat and other ingredients in the machine. She will pop the final 
product into the microwave to warm and serve either on a potato skin or in a 
cup. 
</P>
<P>
 Burk is now busy dreaming up combinations -- maybe one with Caesar dressing, 
cheese, and butter, she said, or another with turkey and gravy. "You can create 
whatever you want," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 As for the yogurt: "We put chocolate or vanilla nonfat yogurt into the 
machine. Then people can choose from all kinds of toppings -- Heath bar crunch, 
chocolate chip cookie dough," Burk said. And combinations, like 
strawberry-banana, can be made by mixing the fruits with the yogurt. The same 
technique is used for the ice cream. 
</P>
<P>
 The cafe is in the Target shopping center at 4020 E. Main St. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ron Fiducia and Scott Hinton are attracting novice coffee drinkers to their 
2-month-old Simi Valley coffeehouse. 
</P>
<P>
 "A lot of people coming in have never had a cappuccino," said Fiducia, an 
experienced coffee guzzler who co-owns the Coffee Connection. "Some have never 
seen a whole bean." 
</P>
<P>
 The entrepreneurs have seen plenty of beans in their time, but they only 
recently learned about what goes into roasting and brewing them. "We had to 
research coffees and machines," said Fiducia who, like Hinton, used to manage a 
finance company. "We spent a lot of time reading books about coffee and about 
what espresso really is." 
</P>
<P>
 Coffee Connection offers 26 roasts and flavors daily, with selections changing 
periodically. 
</P>
<P>
 For now, the establishment also sells some pastries, but the owners are 
looking for a refrigerator large enough to accommodate perishable desserts and 
sandwiches. Coffee Connection is at 1407-X E. Los Angeles Ave., in the HomeBase 
shopping center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
