<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES: A SAMPLER FOR THOSE WITH A TASTE FOR A NIGHT ON THE TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Junior Auxiliary of the Assistance League of Fullerton will hold its 15th 
annual "Taste of the Town" on Sunday from 7 to 10 p.m. at the Brea Mall. Area 
restaurants and caterers -- including Brea Bistro, Giovanni's of Fullerton, 
Portofino's of La Habra and Le Diplomat Cafe of Brea -- are donating 
specialties to sample. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $40 per person for unlimited food, beer and wine; all proceeds of 
ticket sales benefit the Assistance League. Cocktail attire. 
</P>
<P>
 1030 Brea Blvd. For information, call (714) 525-2990. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The OrangeAid Kitchen, a project of area chefs to benefit the Share Our Selves 
homeless shelter in Costa Mesa, will hold a party tonight to celebrate the 
renovation of the kitchen. The evening is also a salute to the 17 participating 
chefs in the annual Kitchen-Aid fund-raiser for SOS, which is April 22. 
</P>
<P>
 Tonight's event, from 6 to 9, is free and open to the public and includes food 
and drink. Tickets will be on sale for the April 22 fund-raiser, at $25 per 
person. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the chefs participating in both events are Michael Kang of Five Feet, 
Alan Greeley of the Golden Truffle, Claude Koeberle of the Ritz and John 
McLaughlin of J.W.'s in the Anaheim Marriott. 
</P>
<P>
 1550 Superior Ave., Costa Mesa. (714) 721-9489. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Carmelo's Ristorante will transform itself into a classroom on Sunday from 5 
to 7 p.m. while students from Corona del Mar High School hold a fund-raiser for 
their school. The high-schoolers will greet customers, take orders, serve the 
food and provide entertainment. The students will be assisting the restaurant's 
chefs a little in the kitchen, too. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds, after costs, will benefit the school; estimates place that amount at 
as much as 50% of customers' bills.  
</P>
<P>
 3520 Pacific Coast Highway, Corona del Mar. For reservations for this event, 
call (310) 491-1000. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Through May 1, Prego Ristorante is celebrating spring with a Festa della 
Primavera, a selection of Italian dishes featuring fresh herbs, vegetables, 
grilled meats and light fruit desserts. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the menu items are calamaretti all'origano (grilled squid served on a 
bed of spinach) for $14.50 and insalata mare e monti (a salad of lightly 
sauteed scallops with porcini mushrooms) for $8.50. 
</P>
<P>
 18420 Von Karman Ave., Irvine. (714) 553-1333. 
</P>
