<HEADLINE>
<P>
OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; THRIFTY TIPS FOR SHOPPING IN RESALE STORES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michelle Pham 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Go often. You never know when a great deal might turn up.Stores receive 
donations throughout the week. 
</P>
<P>
 * Keep an open mind. Look at everything in the store. 
</P>
<P>
 * If you can't alter it yourself, leave it on the rack. 
</P>
<P>
 * Buy clothes you would normally wear. Don't be persuaded by low prices. 
</P>
<P>
 * Look at the lining and stitching of each garment. Search for odors, holes, 
discoloration and snags. 
</P>
<P>
 * Be sure everything fits, because most stores have a no-return policy. 
Michelle Pham 
</P>
</TEXT>
