<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; IN A FOG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 By all accounts, Fullerton High School's recent Pow Wow dance (for the first 
time, a girl-ask-guy affair) was a success.The theme decorations for "A Night 
Under the Canopy" capitalized on a rain forest decor. 
</P>
<P>
 But there were a few glitches, according to the student newspaper, the 
Pleiades.  
</P>
<P>
 "The fog machine didn't work. It started smoking and smelling funny, and this 
tiny little stream of fog came out." 
</P>
<P>
 And, the "deejay flaked on us," he showed up 1 1/2 hours after the dance 
began. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was . . . punctually challenged." 
</P>
